lair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/YF6E4bqe0o6W0V3A.png", "width": 390, "content-type": "png", "height": 680}], "blurhash": "UYPGdHRPx]a#~qj]V@e.IAj?a}WV9Fa#j[oL", "full_resolution": [680, 390]}, "title": "Remigration Now!! 25 Year Old Indian National Arrested for Groping People at a Water Park in Canada!!", "last_comment_created": 1775548986461, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 4, "score_up": 72, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZHdOvKg", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 23, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8541336, "raw_content": ".. or too taboo...\n\nBut I have to say flat earth is one of those things that sounds really convincing at first, and I can see how people get into thinking that way... But then when you go in further, it just doesn't hold up...\n\nAnd another thing I've noticed in terms of sociology is that flat earth honestly seems like a planned way to attack and discredit whole groups of people. Just in organically attach a bunch of \"flat earth\" shit to a group, in an attempt to discredit it.\n\nI think that is happening with MAGA right now, and I also remember it happening during Trump's first term. Another interesting thing is that it used to be they could mock And discredit a group by mocking disbelief in macroevolution. That was 20 years ago though. That one isn't really flying anymore because it's a house of cards that more precise science pokes more holes in every year.\n\nBut anyway.... Flat earthers.... If youre legit, I understand why you're skeptical of everything, and how you could think what you do. But also consider that there are people who use your very distrust and open-mindedness against you. That is what flat earth is.", "author": "HeavenlyTrumpets", "created": 1775536410420, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "me-no-likely3", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "I don't shy away from \"conspiracy\" theories, and have entertained all kinds of \"crazy\" thoughts about history, spiritual things, etc... just to consider them. I even considered flat earth. I looked into a lot, cause I'm not afraid to look at things, and consider things, even if they seem too crazy..", "last_comment_created": 1775542441505, "content": "<p>.. or too taboo...</p>\n<p>But I have to say flat earth is one of those things that sounds really convincing at first, and I can see how people get into thinking that way... But then when you go in further, it just doesn't hold up...</p>\n<p>And another thing I've noticed in terms of sociology is that flat earth honestly seems like a planned way to attack and discredit whole groups of people. Just in organically attach a bunch of &quot;flat earth&quot; shit to a group, in an attempt to discredit it.</p>\n<p>I think that is happening with MAGA right now, and I also remember it happening during Trump's first term. Another interesting thing is that it used to be they could mock And discredit a group by mocking disbelief in macroevolution. That was 20 years ago though. That one isn't really flying anymore because it's a house of cards that more precise science pokes more holes in every year.</p>\n<p>But anyway.... Flat earthers.... If youre legit, I understand why you're skeptical of everything, and how you could think what you do. But also consider that t